    {
      "id": "f139389433b894538236c72abf557e3404535787",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-15 02:07:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nJohn, to answer your question about dead code in wireshark - I suspect relatively little of it is dead, since we typically don't remove features from the network protocol, just add them.\n\nHowever, there was a large batch of removals for the old 1.0-1.8 MDS RPC protocol for maybe the 2.2 or 2.3 release.  Now that you mention it, there is also the \"lustre_msg_v1\" structure which could also be removed, since it was also obsoleted by \"lustre_msg_v2/ptlrpc_body\" back in the 1.8 days.  Maybe a couple of quota structures are obsoleted in 2.4.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "c575385d5b9e5a55a3c3a508e50e56755bfb2e30",
